udata = data[, id_var := paste("ID", "SYMBOL", "POS", "REF", "ALT", sep = "_")]

Threshold

Find max probability and filter out those below 0.6

###CREATE A NEW COLUMN WITH THE HIGHEST PROBABILITY

##TURN SCORE COLUMNS INTO NUMERIC VARIABLES
#SELECT SCORE COLUMNS
score_col = 
  udata %>% 
  select(contains("SCORE")) 

#SELECT COLUMN NAMES
cols.num <- colnames(score_col)

#CONVERT INTO NUMERIC
udata = as.data.frame(udata)
udata[cols.num] <- sapply(udata[cols.num],as.numeric)
NAs introduced by coercionNAs introduced by coercionNAs introduced by coercionNAs introduced by coercion
##SELECT MAX PROBABILITY FROM SPLICEAI OUTPUT
max_data =
  udata %>% 
  mutate(MAX_PROBABILITY = apply(X = data[,10:13], MARGIN = 1, FUN = max)) %>% 
  drop_na(MAX_PROBABILITY)

## GET ANNOTATION COLUMN
ann_ccle = 
CCLE %>%  
  select(Hugo_Symbol, CCLE_Name, Variant_Classification, Variant_annotation)

## FILTER FOR THOSE CLASSIFIED AS ALTERING A SPLICE SITE
CCLE_splice = 
  CCLE %>% 
    filter(Variant_Classification == "Splice_Site")

Join CCLE annotation with spliceAI output

## JOIN BY HUGO SYMBOL AND CELL LINE NAME
ann_data = 
  max_data %>% 
  left_join(ann_ccle, by = "id_var") %>% 
  select(-c("Hugo_Symbol", "QUAL", "FILTER", "CCLE_Name")) #drop unnecessary variables

PREPARE DATA FOR ROC CURVES

Filtering steps (not necessary, just exploration)

## FILTER THOSE WITH HIGH PROBABILITY OF AFFECTING SPLICING (according to spliceAI)
filt_data =
  ann_data %>% 
  filter(MAX_PROBABILITY > 0.6)%>% 
  mutate(Variant_Classification = as_factor(Variant_Classification)) %>% 
  mutate(MAX_PROBABILITY = as.double(MAX_PROBABILITY)) %>% 
  drop_na()

head(filt_data)

#SILENT MUTATIONS / NA
filt_data_miss = 
  filt_data %>% 
  filter(Variant_Classification == "Silent" | Variant_Classification != is.na()) 

# TRUE POSITIVE (SPLICE_SITE)
filt_data_pos = 
  filt_data %>% 
  filter(Variant_Classification == "Splice_Site")

Use Variant_annotation variable instead of Variant_Classification (less levels)

## CONVERT ANNOTATION INTO FACTOR AND PROBABILTY TO DOUBLE 
alt_ann = 
  ann_data %>% 
  mutate(MAX_PROBABILITY = as.double(MAX_PROBABILITY)) %>% 
  drop_na() %>% 
  mutate(Variant_annotation = as_factor(Variant_annotation)) 
Problem with `mutate()` input `MAX_PROBABILITY`.
ℹ NAs introduced by coercion
ℹ Input `MAX_PROBABILITY` is `as.double(MAX_PROBABILITY)`.NAs introduced by coercion
#SEE ANNOTATION
alt_ann %>% 
  select(Variant_annotation) %>% 
  distinct()

## DATA FOR ROC
roc_alt_data = 
  alt_ann %>% 
  mutate(Variants = case_when(
    Variant_annotation == "silent" ~ 0,
    Variant_annotation == "other conserving" ~ 0, 
    Variant_annotation == "other non-conserving" ~ 1, 
    Variant_annotation == "damaging" ~ 1
  ))

ROC curve

Using Variant_annotation as predictor

## PREDICTOR = spliceAI out
## RESPONSE = Variant_annotation


##MULTICLASS ROC: using all levels of Variant_annotation
roc_alt_obj <- multiclass.roc(response = roc_alt_data$Variant_annotation, predictor = roc_alt_data$MAX_PROBABILITY, levels = base::levels(roc_alt_data$Variant_annotation), percent = TRUE)

roc_alt_obj


##NORMAL ROC: using Variant_annotation transformed into a two level factor
rocobj <- roc(response = roc_alt_data$Variants, predictor = roc_alt_data$MAX_PROBABILITY, partial.auc.correct = TRUE, percent = TRUE)

##PLOT
plot.roc(rocobj, print.auc = TRUE)
